/collaborators/\">Collaborators</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li id=\"menu-item-1765\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-has-children menu-item-1765\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/professionalsocial/\">Professional/Social</a>\n<ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1802\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1802\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/professionalsocial/services/\">Services</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1801\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1801\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/professionalsocial/recognitions/\">Recognitions</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1800\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1800\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/professionalsocial/interviews/\">Interviews</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li id=\"menu-item-1774\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-has-children menu-item-1774\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/personal/\">Personal</a>\n<ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1799\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1799\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/personal/past-affiliations/\">Affiliations</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1798\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1798\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/personal/education/\">Education</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1793\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1793\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/personal/favorite-books/\">Favorite Books</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-1797\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-1797\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/personal/favorite-quotes/\">Favorite Quotes</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"default-menu\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu\" title=\"Navigation\">Navigation</a></li></ul></div><!-- .container -->\n\t\t\t\t\t</nav><!-- #access --> \t\t\n\t\t\t\t</header>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"main\" class=\"container clearfix\">\n\n<div id=\"container\">\n\t\n\n<div id=\"primary\" class=\"no-margin-left\">\n   <div id=\"content\">\t<section id=\"post-737\" class=\"post-737 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general-updates\">\n\t\t<article>\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n    \t\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\">\n    \t\t\t\tVidhu Vinod Chopra and Bollywood    \t\t\t</h1><!-- .entry-title -->\n  \t\t\t</header>\n\n  \t\t\t\n  \t\t\t\n  \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-content clearfix\">\n    \t\t\t<p>Yesterday I had a chance to attend screening of\u00c2\u00a0 VV Chopra&#8217;s movie Eklavya and hear his interview and question-answers with him on UCLA campus.\u00c2\u00a0 This was a great experience.</p>\n<p>Mr Chopra is definitely a very different director than others.\u00c2\u00a0 This movie is produced and directed so well that while watching the movie, I never thought that it was a Bollywood production &#8212; even though I new it is.\u00c2\u00a0 Movie is directed, filmed, and produced very professionally.\u00c2\u00a0 It does not devite from the theme and carefully presents the new message about &#8216;dharma&#8217;.</p>\n<p>One of the most interesting thing that Vidhu Vinod Chopra said during interview that he makes movies to satisfy himself.\u00c2\u00a0 He wants to be happy that he made the best that he could.\u00c2\u00a0 Another interesting message that I got wa that he uses the basic model of entrepreneurship in his movies.\u00c2\u00a0 He rewards people based on the success of the movie, rather than contracting them.\u00c2\u00a0 He claimed that this results in allowing him to make movies at reasonable cost.\u00c2\u00a0 And there are good actors who are willing to work under that model.</p>\n<p>I hope that other movie makers in India learn somethings from him and make moview that are in that class.\u00c2\u00a0 He is well aware of the problem.\u00c2\u00a0 He mentioned that Indian audience has not appreciated that movie.\u00c2\u00a0 In fact I was told that many Indians in USA also have made statements like who wants to see a movie in which Amitabh Bachchan plays the role of a security man.\u00c2\u00a0 Maybe the taste of Bollywood people has become so bad that it will take long time for them to get out of total melodrama and overacting in a very poorly produced environment.\u00c2\u00a0 But then everybody has right to enjoy what art they like.</p>\n<p>For me, yesterday evening was one of the best evening that had a Bollywood movie a part of it.\u00c2\u00a0 And I do hope that I see more such movies.</p>\n  \t\t\t</div>\n  \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta-bar clearfix\">\t        \t\t\t\n    \t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n    \t\t\t\t<span class=\"by-author\">By <a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/author/ramesh/\">Ramesh</a></span> |\n    \t\t\t\t<span class=\"date\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/\" title=\"9:15 pm\">March 25, 2007</a></span> |\n    \t\t\t\t             \t\t<span class=\"category\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/category/general-updates/\" rel=\"category tag\">General Updates</a></span> |\n             \t \n    \t\t\t\t             \t\t<span class=\"comments\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/#comments\">4 Comments</a></span> |\n             \t \t\t          \t\t\t\t\n    \t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n    \t\t</div>\n\n  \t\t\t\t\t\t<ul class=\"default-wp-page clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"previous\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/india-in-cricket-world-cup/\" rel=\"prev\"><span class=\"meta-nav\">&larr;</span> India in Cricket World Cup</a></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"next\"><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/long-tail-using-recognition-by-crowds/\" rel=\"next\">Long Tail using Recognition by Crowds <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;</span></a></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\n<div id=\"comments\" class=\"comments-area\">\n\n\t\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"comments-title\">\n\t\t\t4 thoughts on &ldquo;<span>Vidhu Vinod Chopra and Bollywood</span>&rdquo;\t\t</h3>\n\n\t\t<ol class=\"commentlist\">\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"pingback even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-948\">\n\t\t<p>Pingback: <a href='http://desi-galaxy.sabza.org/2007/03/26/news-and-links-round-up/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Desi Galaxy &raquo; News and Links Round up</a> </p>\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-949\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-949\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f5bf86a07357030154418b36fe43de38?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f5bf86a07357030154418b36fe43de38?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.ashishontech.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Ashish Gupta</a> </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/#comment-949\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2007-03-26T09:51:44-07:00\">March 26, 2007 at 9:51 am</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Vidhu is technically a very accompished diretcor. But he and his movies lack ability to connect to people. Connecting to people  is what differentiate a great director (or story teller) from a good one like Vidhu.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment byuser comment-author-ramesh bypostauthor even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-951\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-951\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c7e700ac9901c23d82d2720e3664dbd?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4c7e700ac9901c23d82d2720e3664dbd?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\">Ramesh <span> Post author</span></cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/#comment-951\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2007-03-27T10:56:48-07:00\">March 27, 2007 at 10:56 am</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Maybe Vidhu is not able to connect with Bollywood audience because he is &#8216;too technical&#8217; or &#8216;too sophisticated&#8217; for Bollywood audience of today.  Looking at the stories, direction, acting, and special effects in common Bollywood movies and other programs on ZeeTV, it is clear that there is no other direction but to improve.  Hopefully Bollywood is going to grow rapidly and people like Vidhu V Chopra will be the leaders in this process.<br />\nIn my humble opinion, the problem maybe the place where he is rather than the quality of his work.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"li-comment-4513\">\n\t\t<article id=\"comment-4513\" class=\"comment\">\n\t\t\t<header class=\"comment-meta comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/80c844360562be62c31f5ba0223a4f4c?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/80c844360562be62c31f5ba0223a4f4c?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.filmitadka.in' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Nisha Acharya</a> </cite><a href=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/#comment-4513\"><time pubdate datetime=\"2011-07-21T15:49:09-07:00\">July 21, 2011 at 3:49 pm</time></a>\t\t\t</header><!-- .comment-meta -->\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<section class=\"comment-content comment\">\n\t\t\t\t<p>Saw eklavya and 3 idiots today back to back, and I must say Vidhu excel in both the roles, be it of producer or director. Even when I see interviews conducted by his wife Anupama I experience sincere and cinema literate journalism.</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</section><!-- .comment-content -->\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div><!-- .reply -->\n\t\t</article><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\t\t</ol><!-- .commentlist -->\n\n\t\t\n\t\n\t\t<div id=\"respond\" class=\"comment-respond\">\n\t\t<h3 id=\"reply-title\" class=\"comment-reply-title\">Leave a Reply <small><a rel=\"nofollow\" id=\"cancel-comment-reply-link\" href=\"/vidhu-vinod-chopra-and-bollywood/#respond\" style=\"display:none;\">Cancel reply</a></small></h3>\t\t\t<form action=\"https://ngs.ics.uci.edu/wp-comments-post.php\" method=\"post\" id=\"commentform\" class=\"comment-form\">\n\t\t\t\t<p class=\"comment-notes\"><span id=\"email-notes\">Your email address will not be published.</span> Required fields are marked <span class=\"required\">*</span></p><p class=\"comment-form-comment\"><label for=\"comment\">Comment</label> <textarea id=\"comment\" name=\"comment\" cols=\"45\" rows=\"8\" maxlength=\"65525\" required=\"required\"></textarea></p><p class=\"comment-form-author\"><label for=\"author\">Name <span class=\"required\">*</span></label> <input id=\"author\" name=\"author\" type=\"text\" value=\"\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"245\" required='required' /></p>\n<p class=\"comment-form-email\"><label for=\"email\">Email <span class=\"required\">*</span></label> <input id=\"email\" name=\"email\" type=\"text\" value=\"\" size=\"30\" maxlength=\"100\" aria-describedby=\"email-notes\" required='required' /></p>\n<p class=\"comme